{"actual_usd":0.12426,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":185,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24297,"reply":"\"I wouldn't start with which one feels roomy, Ryan.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron and glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"I'd start with which one asks the truest thing about what happened. If Christ truly rose, then a merely metaphorical frame is too small; if he didn't, then calling it literal because it comforts or organizes life is too big.\"\n\n*I let that sit a beat, the bench giving a faint creak under me.* \"So I think the question is less 'which framework fits me?' and more 'what can bear the weight of reality, conscience, Scripture, and the kind of God you believe you're dealing with?' If you want, we can walk through the literal, metaphorical, and broad-inclusive readings one by one and see where each one holds... and where it starts to go thin.\"","rolling_24h_usd":88.62893000000001,"run_id":"0cf2f29f-24c2-444a-b9fa-3bb30233e117"}
